sql:
SELECT COUNT(view_id) AS total_views
FROM item_views
WHERE item_id = 1;

SELECT name, average_rating
FROM items
ORDER BY average_rating DESC;

SELECT MAX(price) AS highest_price
FROM items
WHERE is_active = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "ocean of reviews" is a metaphor for the extensive feedback data;
- "electronic gem" refers to items in the "Electronics" category;
- "admired by at least a small crowd of ten voices" means there are at least ten feedback entries.

- 'typical score' refers to the average_score of the score values generated by each algorithm;
- 'most recent evaluation date' is the latest_score_date when the scores were last calculated;
- 'general satisfaction level' is represented by the average_item_rating, which reflects the average user ratings for the items evaluated by the respective algorithms.

sql:
SELECT AVG(rating) AS average_rating
FROM feedback
WHERE rating IS NOT NULL;

SELECT i.item_id, i.name, i.average_rating
FROM items i
WHERE i.average_rating = (SELECT MAX(average_rating) FROM items);

SELECT item_id, name, average_rating
FROM items
ORDER BY average_rating DESC;
